.TH "cgroup_calc_subtree_ss_mask" 9 "cgroup_calc_subtree_ss_mask" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cgroup_calc_subtree_ss_mask \- calculate subtree_ss_mask
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u16" cgroup_calc_subtree_ss_mask
.BI "(u16 subtree_control "  ","
.BI "u16 this_ss_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "subtree_control" 12
the new subtree_control mask to consider
.IP "this_ss_mask" 12
available subsystems
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
On the default hierarchy, a subsystem may request other subsystems to be
enabled together through its ->depends_on mask.  In such cases, more
subsystems than specified in "cgroup.subtree_control" may be enabled.

This function calculates which subsystems need to be enabled if
\fIsubtree_control\fP is to be applied while restricted to \fIthis_ss_mask\fP.
